# CODEOWNERS — review ownership mapped to the architecture's lanes.
#
# Purpose: make the *social* boundary match the *code* boundary so TOPAZ
# (single-crystal) and USANS (SANS) can be developed in parallel. A change that
# stays inside one technique/beamline lane is reviewed by that lane's owner; a
# change to the shared trunk (core/app/agent) or the manifest contract pulls in
# a framework reviewer automatically.
#
# Enforcement of the *import* boundaries that back this up lives in
# tests/test_import_boundaries.py (CI-blocking).
#
# NOTE: the handles below are PLACEHOLDERS. Replace them with real GitHub
# usernames or @org/team slugs for CODEOWNERS to take effect (GitHub silently
# ignores unknown owners). Until then this file documents the intended lanes.

# ---- Shared trunk: affects every technique → framework review ----------------
/src/exphub/core/      @framework-team
/src/exphub/app/       @framework-team
/src/exphub/agent/     @framework-team

# The manifest is the agent+shell API between a technique and the framework.
# Changing it is an API change — always framework-reviewed.
/src/exphub/core/beamline/technique.py   @framework-team

# ---- Single-crystal lane (TOPAZ, CORELLI) -----------------------------------
/src/exphub/techniques/single_crystal/   @single-crystal-team
/src/exphub/beamlines/topaz/             @single-crystal-team
/src/exphub/beamlines/corelli/           @single-crystal-team
/tests/techniques/single_crystal/        @single-crystal-team

# ---- SANS lane (USANS) ------------------------------------------------------
/src/exphub/techniques/sans/   @sans-team
/src/exphub/beamlines/usans/   @sans-team
/tests/techniques/sans/        @sans-team

# ---- Cross-cutting test/process guards → framework review -------------------
/tests/test_import_boundaries.py     @framework-team
/tests/test_technique_coupling.py    @framework-team
/tests/test_beamline_coupling.py     @framework-team
/tests/test_acceptance.py            @framework-team
/.github/                            @framework-team
/pyproject.toml                      @framework-team
